  "prompt": "Can a foreign citizen open a savings bank account, in India?",
  "response": "Yes, a foreign citizen can open a savings bank account in India, but with certain conditions and documentation requirements:\n\n1. For Non-Resident Indians (NRIs):\n- Can open Non-Resident External (NRE) or Non-Resident Ordinary (NRO) accounts\n- Easier process with minimal restrictions\n\n2. For Foreign Nationals:\n- Can open accounts with proper documentation\n- Must comply with Reserve Bank of India (RBI) guidelines\n- Typically require:\n   * Valid passport\n   * Visa\n   * Proof of local address\n   * PAN card or Tax Identification Number\n   * Proof of income\n   * Photographs\n   * Completed Know Your Customer (KYC) forms\n\n3. Types of Accounts:\n- Regular Savings Account\n- NRE Account\n- NRO Account\n\n4. Important Considerations:\n- Different banks may have varying specific requirements\n- Some banks might have additional documentation needs\n- Purpose of stay in India can impact account opening process\n\n5. Recommendations:\n- Check specific bank's requirements\n- Consult with bank representatives\n- Ensure all documentation is in order\n\nThe process can vary slightly depending on the specific bank and individual circumstances.",
